@SuperQ

> Do you want to take a first pass

Sure - I can try and fit this in over the next couple days.

> If the metrics handler doubles as a Caddy HTTP handler module like I described, then the listening port and path are all taken care of by the user's config, no need to separately configure tha
```yaml
{
  "apps": {
    "http": {
      "servers": {
        "srv0": {
          "listen": [ ":9180" ],
          "routes": {
            "match": [{ "path": [ "/metrics" ] }],
            "handle": [{ "handler": "prometheus" }],
            "terminal": true
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```
